The paper deals with facial behavior analysis tasks in computer vision, which is a typical topic in the computer vision subfield. The paper proposes a unified framework for simultaneous facial landmark detection, head pose estimation, and facial deformation analysis, which involves machine learning and deep learning techniques. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves iterative updates and model-based head pose estimation, which suggests that it may belong to the sub-categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also deals with facial occlusion, which is a common problem in multimedia analysis, suggesting that it may belong to the sub-categories of cs.MM (Multimedia) and cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction).
